OL,3,CCalls for adequate compensation for
OL,4,Cveterans who suffered under 'gay ban'
OL,6,FSurvivors of the scandal suffered days
OL,7,Fof sometimes brutal interrogation when
OL,8,Fit was discovered they were gay; many
OL,9,Fwere dismissed from the forces, lost
OL,10,Fout on job opportunities and were
OL,11,Fshunned by families and friends.
OL,13,FAn independent review into the service
OL,14,Fand experience of LGBT veterans who
OL,15,Fserved prior to 2000, led by Lord
OL,16,FEtherton, recommended a #50 million
OL,17,Fcap on the total sum of compensation.
